SIMPLE: retirement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retirement
<hw>Re*tire"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>retirement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of retiring, or
the state of being retired; withdrawal; seclusion; <as>as, the
<ex>retirement</ex> of an officer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, blest <qex>Retirement</qex>, friend of life's decline.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Retirement</qex>, rural quiet, friendship, books.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place of seclusion or privacy; a place to which
one withdraws or retreats; a private abode.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This coast full of princely <qex>retirements</qex> for the
sumptousness of their buildings and nobleness of the plantations.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Caprea had been the <qex>retirement</qex> of Augustus.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Solitude; withdrawment; departure; retreat;
seclusion; privacy. See <er>Solitude</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retirer</ent>⟦br⟧
